This device was previously known (as in, before launch) as the N9+.
The FCC photos appear to show the device with 2x ''Nanya'' RAM chips :NT5TU64M16DG-AC (128MB each, 256MB total). The board is also shown as covered with a large heatsink :(similarly to the [[ASUS RT-N66U]]). The device is presumed to be fully ''[[Broadcom]]'' based..
Default credentials are per the FCC manual/installation guide.
===Forum threads=== *[http://www.linksysinfo.org/index.php?threads/tenda-n80-tomato-firmware-support.71831/ ''Tenda N80 - Tomato firmware support'' on '''linksysinfo''' forums] :There appear to be two different Flash memory versions of this router: :• WL Driver version 5x has 8 MiB of flash memory (part number MX25L6408E) :• WL Driver version 6x has 16 MiB of flash memory
